# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 uses a simple `[INST]`/`[/INST]` chat format that differs from the more complex Ministral 3 format (which has `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, `[TOOL_CALLS]`, `[ARGS]`). A new specialized handler is needed to support this simpler format. Only `common/chat.cpp` needs modification; no changes to `common/chat.h`.

## File to Modify

- `common/chat.cpp`

## Step 1: Add Handler Function (insert after line 1517, before `namespace workaround` at line 1519)

Add `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3` — a simple handler that manually builds the prompt string by iterating `inputs.messages`. No PEG parser, no grammar, no tool support.

```cpp
